<DOC><DOCNO> AP890911-0120 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-11-89 1911EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-LionDeath     09-11 0225</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Lion Death,0231</SECOND><HEAD>Mountain Lion Kills Youngster</HEAD><DATELINE>EVARO, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 5-year-old boy last seen riding histricycle near his home was killed by a mountain lion that was latertracked down and killed, authorities said Monday.   The body of Jake Gardipe was found Sunday night just 30 yardsfrom his home, said Missoula County Sheriff's Lt. Greg Hintz.   Tracking dogs later found a female mountain lion nearby that wasthen shot, said Rick Schoening, a game warden for the MontanaDepartment of Fish, Wildlife and Parks. The animal had blood in itsmouth and claws, he said.   Jake was last seen at 3 p.m. Sunday, playing near his rural hometwo miles north of the tiny community of Evaro in mountainouswestern Montana. He was reported missing shortly before 7 p.m. andhis body was found a short time later.   Fish and Wildlife officials for the Confederated Salish andKootenai Tribes, whose reservation boundary runs through Evaro,joined Missoula County Search and Rescue members in looking for theboy.   Residents have spotted two mountain lions in the area recentlyand reported that two dogs have been killed.   Efforts were made Monday to catch the other lion, Hintz said.   Two fatal lion attacks have been reported in recent years inCalifornia, Kerry Murphy of the Wildlife Research Institute atYellowstone National Park said.</TEXT></DOC>